// @test regression/INV105-tuple-call-to-scalar
// @description A tuple-returning USER function bound to a single variable (`a = f()` where `f` returns `[1, 2]`) is TV's CE10092 - a tuple can only be destructured. Destructuring (`[a, b] = f()`) and a scalar-returning call stay clean. Probed 2026-06-25 via pine-lint --tv, see INV105.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=4, message=/Cannot assign a tuple to a variable "a"/
// @expects errors: 1

//@version=6
indicator("INV105-tuple-call-to-scalar")
f() => [1, 2]
a = f()
[p, q] = f()
g() => 7
y = g()
plot(p + q + y)
